name: L-methionine (R)-S-oxide reductase
classes: Acting on a sulfur group of donors;
reaction: L-methionine + thioredoxin disulfide + H2O = L-methionine (R)-S-oxide + thioredoxin [RN:R07608]
comment: Requires NADPH. Unlike EC 1.8.4.12, peptide-methionine (R)-S-oxide reductase, this enzyme cannot use peptide-bound methionine (R)-S-oxide as a substrate [1]. Differs from EC 1.8.4.13, L-methionine (S)-S-oxide in that L-methionine (S)-S-oxide is not a substrate.

references.title: A methionine sulfoxide reductase in Escherichia coli that reduces the R enantiomer of methionine sulfoxide.
